<!--100-->All Blades Perish x2.    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">The deck is a real nuisance. <br />
Use WAWWF, CIITTF, and CTFF to screw with their hand (if you are not playing orcs, use CTFF to nuke conditions). The companions are decent fighters, but that is not the intentions of this deck. Glorfindel should be able to take on any strong minion that gets through the sabotage.<br />
<br />
The shadow side is a complete hand clogger. grima+lemenya+SSA = clogged hand..<br />
with the slight choking abilities of the free peeps, and all the hand &quot;harrassing&quot;, this shadow side should slow down you opponents set up to a crawl.<br />
This shadow is just a way to stop your opponent, not kill it. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
